        <head type="scenarioTitle" xml:lang="en">Doing 3D reconstruction in archaeological context</head>
        <desc type="definition" xml:lang="en"> 3D reconstructions have a long history in archaeology
          and cultural heritage, although there are varying practices, data capture and processing
          methods, tools, and visualisations. There are not clear ways of determining the accuracy
          and precision of the reconstructions. Furthermore, scientifics and engagement purposes
          inform different dissemination practices, and therefore pose different challenges to the
          preservation of these outputs. </desc>
